main event: Navy personnel observed multiple unidentified flying objects over La Jolla, California on 15 October 1957.
interesting points: The observation lasted for approximately 30 minutes,There were reports of up to 3 objects observed spinning and traveling at an estimated speed of 600-700 mph,The objects were reported as being 40-50 feet in diameter with a silver or light color,Multiple sightings on different dates corroborated the presence of unidentified lights in the sky, The reports indicated that the sightings were assessed as being possibly more than celestial phenomena.
witness description: Navy personnel and credible citizens in the area
